{"name": "hydraters", "metadata": {"name": "hydraters", "version": "0.1.2", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Programming Language :: Rust"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Hydrate Python dictionaries with Rust.", "upload_time": 1733257316}, "documentation": ["# hydraters\n\n[![GitHub Actions Workflow Status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/developmentseed/hydraters/pr.yaml?style=for-the-badge)](https://github.com/developmentseed/hydraters/actions/workflows/pr.yaml)\n[![PyPI - Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/hydraters?style=for-the-badge)](https://pypi.org/project/hydraters/)\n\nHydrate Python dictionaries with Rust.\nA general-purpose algorithm, used in [pgstac](https://github.com/stac-utils/pgstac) to reduce the size of the `items` table.\n\n```python\nimport hydraters\n\nbase = {\"a\": \"first\", \"b\": \"second\", \"c\": {\"d\": \"third\"}}\nitem = {\"c\": {\"e\": \"fourth\", \"f\": \"fifth\"}}\nresult = hyrdraters.hydrate(base, item)\nassert result == {\n    \"a\": \"first\",\n    \"b\": \"second\",\n    \"c\": {\"d\": \"third\", \"e\": \"fourth\", \"f\": \"fifth\"},\n}\n```\n\n## Installation\n\n```shell\npython -m pip install hydraters\n```\n\nOr, if you're using **uv**:\n\n```shell\nuv add hydraters\n```\n\n## Developing\n\nGet [Rust](https://rustup.rs/) and [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/).\nThen:\n\n```shell\ngit clone git@github.com:developmentseed/hydraters.git\ncd hydraters\nuv sync\nuv run pre-commit install\n```\n\nTo run tests:\n\n```shell\nuv run pytest\n```\n\n## Background\n\nThe code for this package was taken from [pypgstac](https://github.com/stac-utils/pgstac/blob/f1d71d5e00392acb970e3b19a62d5f1aa8d50cc6/src/pypgstac/src/lib.rs).\nIt came from some [benchmarking](https://github.com/gadomski/json-hydrate-benchmark) that determined it was much faster to do this operation in Rust than in pure Python.\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_dehydrate", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_single_depth_equals", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_nested_equals", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_nested_extra_keys", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_list_of_dicts_extra_keys", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_equal_len_list_of_mixed_types", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_unequal_len_list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Test that unequal length lists preserve the item value exactly."]}, {"name": "tests.test_dehydrate.test_marked_non_merged_fields", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null